04:31 Defendant Joseph R. Kogut in court. Atty Shelly Tomtschik appears via phone for the defendant.  Rory Eoin O'Sullivan appeared for the State of Wisconsin. O'Sullivan: plead to count 1, S/W 1 year, $500 in restitution within 30 days of today's date, if not paid defendant will serve 7 days conditional jail time w/o work release and retitution will go to $1600 due over the course of probation. Parties agree. Defendant wishes to proceed with his attorney via phone. Court does the plea questionnaire and waiver of rights with defendant on the record.  Constitutional rights explained to defendant.  Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights.  DEF PLEADS GUILTY.  Facts are correct.  COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS.  The court finds the defendant guilty and adjudicates defendant guilty. Parties address the court. Court orders: S/W 1 year, $500 restitution due in 30 days --5/6/17, if not paid in full by 5/6/17 restitution will then go to the amount of $1600 due over the course of probation and defendant will have to report to PCJ 5/7/17 to serve 7 days conditional jail time, no work release, follow conditions by agent, court costs dna sample surcharge $443 due over probation.
